    <note>Wang(1) Hua [15627] He was orphaned when young and traveled to Kuaiji where his uncle was a general serving Sui and learned military skills. After he returned to Huizhou, he raised a milita and cleared Wuyuan county of bandits during the troubles that marked the last years of Sui. He rose to high office in Tang and died and was buried in Changan, but his sons and grandsons moved the body to Xixian. Huizhou FZ, 7.2a-2b.</note>
